# Home Inventory Manager — SRS Rules

## Project Overview

**App:** Home Inventory Manager  
**Purpose:** Mobile app for tracking household assets, warranties, receipts, maintenance schedules, and insurance documents.  
**Target users:** Homeowners, renters, families, property managers, small business owners.  
**MVP timeline:** 2–3 months. Design for later commercial growth.

## Core Objectives

Every feature must support at least one of:

- Digital inventory of household items
- Warranty and purchase tracking
- Receipt and insurance document storage
- Reminders (warranty expiration, maintenance)
- Fast search and asset location
- Reports for insurance claims or home audits

## Technology Stack (Required)

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Mobile | Flutter |
| State management | **bloc** (do not use GetX, Provider-only, or Riverpod unless explicitly approved) |
| Backend | Firebase + Node.js (where server logic is needed) |
| Database | Firebase Firestore + SQLite (local/offline) |
| Storage | Firebase Storage |
| Auth | Firebase Authentication (JWT-based sessions) |
| Notifications | Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) |
| AI (Premium) | OpenAI API, Google Vision API, Barcode Lookup API |

## Architecture

Follow **Clean Architecture** with strict layer separation:

```
lib/
├── main.dart
├── core/           # constants, theme, routing, errors, utils
├── features/
│   └── <feature>/
│       ├── data/       # datasources, repositories, DTOs
│       ├── domain/     # entities, repository interfaces, use cases
│       └── presentation/  # bloc, pages, widgets
└── shared/         # cross-feature widgets and services
```

- Use **repository pattern** for all data access (Firestore, SQLite, Storage, APIs).
- Keep business logic in domain/use cases and blocs — not in widgets.
- Use DTOs for API/Firestore serialization; map to domain entities in repositories.

## User Roles

| Role | Capabilities |
|------|--------------|
| **Standard User** | Full CRUD on own inventory, documents, reminders, reports |
| **Family Member** (future) | View shared inventory; add/update items |
| **Admin** (future) | User management, subscriptions, analytics |

Implement role checks at repository/service layer, not only in UI.

